[1595.884885, "o", "\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[1595.921716, "o", "\u001b[?1049h\u001b[22;0;0t\u001b[?1h\u001b=\r"]
[1595.947238, "o", "\u001b[4mCRYPTTAB\u001b[24m(5)                      cryptsetup manual                     \u001b[4mCRYPTTAB\u001b[24m(5)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       crypttab - static information about encrypted filesystems\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       The file /etc/crypttab contains descriptive information about encrypted\u001b[m\r\n       devices. crypttab is only read by programs (e.g. \u001b[1mcryptdisks_start \u001b[22mand\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mcryptdisks_stop\u001b[22m), and not written; it is the duty of the system\u001b[m"]
[1595.947421, "o", "\r\n       administrator to properly create and maintain this file. crypttab entries\u001b[m\r\n       are treated sequentially, so their order matters (dependencies need to\u001b[m\r\n       listed first).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m"]
[1595.947471, "o", "\r\n       Each encrypted device is described on a separate line. Fields on each line\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 1 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1598.484059, "o", "\r\u001b[K       are separated by tabs or spaces. Lines starting with '#' are comments, and\u001b[m\r\n       blank lines are ignored. Octal sequences \\0\u001b[4mnum\u001b[24m within a field are decoded,\u001b[m\r\n       which can be used for values containing spaces or special characters. A\u001b[m\r\n       backslash which doesn't start an octal sequence yields undefined behavior.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       The first field, \u001b[4mtarget\u001b[24m, describes the mapped device name. It must be a\u001b[m\r\n       plain filename without any directory components. A mapped device which\u001b[m\r\n       encrypts/decrypts data to/from the \u001b[4msource\u001b[24m \u001b[4mdevice\u001b[24m will be created at\u001b[m\r\n       /dev/mapper/target by \u001b[1mcryptsetup\u001b[22m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       The second field, \u001b[4msource\u001b[24m \u001b[4mdevice\u001b[24m, describes either the block special device\u001b[m\r\n       or file that contains the encrypted data. Instead of giving the \u001b[4msource\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[4mdevice\u001b[24m explicitly, the UUID (resp. LABEL, PARTUUID and PARTLABEL) is\u001b[m\r\n       supported as well, using вҖңUUID=<uuid>вҖқ (resp. вҖңLABEL=<label>вҖқ,\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 15 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1601.640709, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       вҖңPARTUUID=<partuuid>вҖқ and вҖңPARTLABEL=<partlabel>вҖқ).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 16 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1601.700965, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 17 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1611.772868, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       The third field, \u001b[4mkey\u001b[24m \u001b[4mfile\u001b[24m, describes the file to use as a key for\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 18 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1613.731093, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       decrypting the data of the \u001b[4msource\u001b[24m \u001b[4mdevice\u001b[24m. In case of a \u001b[4mkeyscript\u001b[24m, the value\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 19 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1618.450838, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       of this field is given as argument to the keyscript. Note that the \u001b[4mentire\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 20 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1618.488473, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       key file will be used as the passphrase; the passphrase must \u001b[4mnot\u001b[24m be\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 21 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1618.527521, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       followed by a newline character.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 22 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1618.955982, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 23 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1618.974881, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       It can also be a device name (e.g. /dev/urandom), note however that LUKS\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 24 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1619.416576, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       requires a persistent key and therefore does \u001b[4mnot\u001b[24m support random data keys.\u001b[m"]
[1619.416679, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 25 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1619.475974, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 26 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1627.71772, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       If the \u001b[4mkey\u001b[24m \u001b[4mfile\u001b[24m is the string \u001b[4mnone\u001b[24m, a passphrase will be read interactively\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 27 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1643.19605, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[1643.196138, "o", "       from the console. In this case, the options check, checkargs and tries may\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 28 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1643.999245, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       be useful.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 29 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1644.71019, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 30 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1645.247851, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       The fourth field, \u001b[4moptions\u001b[24m, is an optional comma-separated list of options\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 31 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1645.32564, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       and/or flags describing the device type (\u001b[4mluks\u001b[24m, \u001b[4mtcrypt\u001b[24m, \u001b[4mbitlk\u001b[24m, \u001b[4mfvault2\u001b[24m, or\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 32 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1654.150529, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       \u001b[4mplain\u001b[24m which is also the default) and cryptsetup options associated with the\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 33 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1654.213311, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       encryption process. The supported options are described below. For plain\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 34 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1654.313732, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       dm-crypt devices the \u001b[4mcipher\u001b[24m, \u001b[4mhash\u001b[24m and \u001b[4msize\u001b[24m options are required. Some\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 35 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1654.677863, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       options can be changed on active mappings using \u001b[1mcryptsetup refresh\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 36 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1654.719344, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       \u001b[1m[<options>] <name>\u001b[22m. Furthermore some options can be permanently written\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 37 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1654.760741, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       into metadata of LUKS2 headers using cryptsetup's \u001b[4m--persistent\u001b[24m flag.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page crypttab(5) line 38 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[1660.887773, "o", "\r\u001b[K\u001b[?1l\u001b>\u001b[?1049l\u001b[23;0;0t"]
[1660.889735, "o", "\u001b[?2004h\u001b]0;root@ubse: ~\u0007root@ubse:~# "]
